###### Installation Instructions ######

+++ Configuring the App +++

When you first install Splunk for Cisco Security, you will have to edit the app's conf files.

The app requires you to have one or more of the supported add-ons installed:

	* Splunk for Cisco Firewalls (ASA or PIX)
	http://splunk-base.splunk.com/apps/22303/splunk-for-cisco-firewalls
	http://splunk-base.splunk.com/answers/3366/how-do-i-install-the-cisco-firewall-add-on
	
	* Splunk for Cisco IPS SDEE
	http://splunk-base.splunk.com/apps/22292/splunk-for-cisco-ips
	http://splunk-base.splunk.com/answers/3364/how-do-i-install-the-cisco-ips-add-on
	
	* Splunk for Cisco IronPort Web Security
	http://splunk-base.splunk.com/apps/22302/splunk-for-cisco-ironport-web-security-appliance
	http://splunk-base.splunk.com/answers/3362/how-do-i-install-and-configure-the-splunk-for-ironport-web-app-on-splunkbase
	
	* Splunk for Cisco IronPort E-Mail Security
	http://splunk-base.splunk.com/apps/22305/splunk-for-cisco-ironport-email-security-appliance
	http://splunk-base.splunk.com/answers/3360/how-do-i-install-the-cisco-ironport-e-mail-add-on
	
Additionally, you will need to install the Google Maps app for the maps to work:

	http://splunk-base.splunk.com/apps/22365/google-maps

###### Troubleshooting the App ######

Below are solutions for common issues:

+++ No Data is Present in the Reports/Dashboards +++

You'll need to install at least one of the other apps or add-ons in order to populate Splunk for Cisco Security with data. See the section "Installation Instructions" above for information about how to obtain the necessary apps and add-ons.

+++ The Maps do not Populate +++

You'll need to install the Google Maps app in order for the maps to populate with data. Install the Google Maps app from:
http://splunk-base.splunk.com/apps/22365/google-maps

